President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Nebraska due to severe storms, winter storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from October 2-6, 2013. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Elizabeth Turner has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.